1. d4 d5 {The symmetrical reply is one of the most common replies. Black places a pawn in the centre just like White.} 2. Nf3 Bf5 {In order to keep the move-order transpositions and possible confusion to a minimum, we point out the possible transpositions in the text below.} ({➢ For example, after} 2... Bf5 3. e3 e6 4. Be2 Nf6 {, we have a transposition to the line after StartFENrnbqkbnr/ppp1pppp/8/3p4/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 2EndFEN 2...Nf6 3.e3 Bf5 4.Be2 e6 .}) ({➢ Similar is} 2... e6 3. e3 Nf6 {, which is examined after StartFENrnbqkbnr/ppp1pppp/8/3p4/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 2EndFEN 2...Nf6 3.e3 e6 .}) ({➢ As is} 2... c6 3. e3 Nf6 {examined after StartFENrnbqkbnr/ppp1pppp/8/3p4/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 2EndFEN 2...Nf6 3.e3 c6 .}) ({➢} 2... c5 3. e3 Nc6 4. Be2 Nf6 {is checked via the move order StartFENrnbqkbnr/ppp1pppp/8/3p4/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 2EndFEN 2...Nf6 3.e3 c5 4.Be2 Nc6 .}) ({➢ Finally,} 2... Bg4 3. e3 Nf6 4. Be2 {is examined after StartFENrnbqkbnr/ppp1pppp/8/3p4/3P4/5N2/PPP1PPPP/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 2EndFEN 2...Nf6 3.e3 Bg4 4.Be2 .}) 3. e3 e6 4. Be2 Nf6 *

